{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"graceless-hominine-jerboa","description":"# Remediate validated findings from the behavioral/contractual test-coverage audit\n\nAn external test-coverage audit (static, pinned to commit `2d1524ad8`) identified a\ncluster of tests that assert against **source text / private structure / mere\nexistence** rather than behavior (\"change-detector\" tests), plus several documented\ncontracts with **no behavioral regression test**, and two documentation-vs-code\ndrifts. We re-verified every finding against the actual codebase with five\nindependent review passes: **all findings validated** (two downgraded to\n\"partial — the mechanism is partly tested but the specific gap is real\"), and the\ngrep-against-source inventory surfaced **additional** anti-pattern tests beyond the\nreport's list.\n\nThis epic converts the false-confidence regressions into real behavioral coverage,\nadds the missing data-safety/concurrency tests, hardens two thin production paths the\naudit exposed, and reconciles the stale docs.\n\n## Context\n\n- The audit's core thesis is correct: the largest residual risk is **not** broad\n  lack of testing — core coverage (CRUD parity, deterministic replay, two-clone\n  reconvergence, no-loss writer storms, claim contention, detector verdict\n  semantics) is strong — but **false confidence** in narrowly-targeted regressions\n  whose tests inspect source structure instead of exercising the promised behavior.\n- Verification method: five parallel read-only audit passes over production source,\n  existing tests, docs, and CI config. Findings that were already covered were\n  dropped; only genuinely-missing/miswired coverage is ticketed here.\n- Grep-against-source is **not** universally an anti-pattern here: 59 of 77\n  source-inspecting tests are JUSTIFIED (the source text *is* the observable\n  contract — exact git argv an adapter builds, layering/import invariants via\n  `ast.parse`, prompt/YAML/Terraform/CI \"config-as-artifact\" drift guards,\n  runtime-produced artifacts). This epic only touches the ~9 ANTI-PATTERN and the\n  handful of BORDERLINE cases where a behavioral test is feasible and stronger.\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n- [ ] Every P0 finding (index.lock stale-reclaim TOCTOU; detached-HEAD local-ahead\n      preservation) has a deterministic behavioral regression test, and the\n      production path is hardened where the race is real.\n- [ ] Each \"change-detector\" regression test named by the audit is either replaced\n      by a behavioral test that fails when the behavior breaks, deleted as redundant\n      (a behavioral sibling already covers it), or explicitly re-justified as a\n      supplemental structural guard — never left counted as behavioral coverage.\n- [ ] The two documentation drifts (Jira link-sync inventory; dual-lock portability\n      lifecycle) are reconciled so contract-to-test traceability is trustworthy.\n- [ ] `make lint && make typecheck && make test` stays green; no net loss of\n      meaningful coverage.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] All child stories are closed (signed), each landing through the Gerrit gate\n      (LLM-Review +1 AND Verified +1).\n- [ ] No test in the changed set asserts only `hasattr(...)`, an exact private\n      constant value, or a source substring where the underlying behavior is\n      executable and was previously untested.\n- [ ] Newly-added concurrency/race tests are deterministic (barrier/instrumented\n      seams, not sleep-timing races that can pass on a slow runner).","id":"bf50-2131-271b-4fdc","parent_id":"","priority":1,"tags":["test-coverage","audit-remediation","quality"],"ticket_type":"epic","title":"Remediate validated findings from the test-coverage audit"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783784655752363001,"uuid":"7f9a9f31-deae-4e1b-bde7-c4e0e98fda9b"}